01/03/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Dora Bakoyannis, Greece's new foreign minister, held talks Tuesday (28 February) at the headquarters of the EU and NATO in Brussels, confirming her country's strong interest in the Balkans. On Thursday, she begins a tour of the region, including stops in Belgrade, Pristina and Sarajevo.
In other news Tuesday, much of Greece was affected by a four-hour strike involving Olympic Airways and railroad workers. The unions are planning 24-hour strike on 15 March. (ANA, ERT AP, Reuters - 28/02/06) 
